.TH JOB-ASSETS-CODEX 1 "March 2026" "job-assets-codex" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
job-assets-codex \- run the job-assets CLI with Codex as the default provider
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B job-assets-codex
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B job-assets-codex
\fIJD_SOURCE\fR [\fICOMPANY\fR] [\fIROLE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B job-assets-codex
behaves like
.BR job-assets ,
but defaults the provider to
.BR codex .
Its Codex-backed runs explicitly request
.B gpt-5.4
with
.B model_reasoning_effort="xhigh"
unless
.BR CODEX_MODEL ,
.BR CODEX_REASONING_EFFORT ,
.BR CODEX_APPROVAL_POLICY ,
.BR CODEX_SANDBOX_MODE ,
 .BR CODEX_PROFILE ,
or
.BR CODEX_EXTRA_ARGS
override them.
When
.B CODEX_PROFILE
is set and the explicit
.B CODEX_*
execution overrides are unset, the CLI defers model, reasoning, approval, and sandbox selection to that profile the same way the interactive Codex TUI does. Non-interactive Codex runs also use a temporary
.B CODEX_HOME
that keeps auth plus sanitized config but strips user
.B mcp_servers
entries so repo automation does not start unrelated desktop MCP servers.
If the first argument is a job description URL or file path, it runs the single-job
.B pipeline
flow and stops at review unless
.B --submit
is also present.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B job-assets-codex https://boards.greenhouse.io/company/jobs/12345
Run the end-to-end single-job flow with Codex.
.TP
.B job-assets-codex --submit https://boards.greenhouse.io/company/jobs/12345
Run the end-to-end single-job flow with Codex and submit after review.
.TP
.B job-assets-codex parallel --max-parallel 8
Run the parallel batch workflow with Codex.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR job-assets (1),
.BR job-assets-claude (1)
